doc.after: A scimitar propeller is shaped like a scimitar sword with increasing sweep along the leading edge Typically scimitar propellers are constructed of lightweight or composite materials In the early 1900s they were made of laminated wood The combination of light weight and efficient aerodynamics results in more power and reduced noise
